**Mathematical proof that screen count is reasonable:**

```markdown
## Screen Count Verification

### Source Documents
- PRD Features: [X] (from /docs/specs/MASTER_PRD.md)
- Flow Tree Screens: [N] (from /docs/flows/SCREEN-INVENTORY.md)

### Calculation
| Category | Count | Expected Range | Status |
|----------|-------|----------------|--------|
| PRD Features | [X] | ‚Äî | ‚Äî |
| Average Screens per Feature | [N/X] | 1.5 - 4.0 | ‚úÖ / ‚ö†Ô∏è |
| Total Screens | [N] | [X√ó1.5] - [X√ó4.0] | ‚úÖ / ‚ö†Ô∏è |

### Red Flags (Investigate if present)
- [ ] Avg screens per feature < 1.5 ‚Üí **Likely missing screens**
- [ ] Features with only 1 screen ‚Üí **Verify sufficient coverage**
- [ ] Error states not counted ‚Üí **Add error/empty state screens**
- [ ] Platform-specific screens missing ‚Üí **Add launch, permissions, etc.**
```

